The paper deals with the nonnegative and positive semidefinite extension complexities of a polytope, which are related to optimization and computational geometry. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) are likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the mutual information of a matrix, which falls under the scope of cs.IT (Information Theory). The analysis of bounds on the PSD-rank involves linear and SDP programs, which are related to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
